Intrinio API

Overview

Welcome to the Intrinio API! We offer a wide selection of fundamental, financial, price data, and economic data. The primary application of the Intrinio API is for use in third-party applications and integrations or for end-users utilizing the Excel add-in and Google Sheets add-on.

The Intrinio API uses HTTP verbs and a RESTful endpoint structure, which makes it easy to request data from Intrinio.  Basic Authentication is administered over HTTPS.  Responses are delivered in JSON format.

If you need additional help in using the API, send us a message by clicking the Help widget in the bottom right corner at anytime.

API Endpoints

All URLs referenced in this documentation have the following base url:

https://api.intrinio.com/

Below is a summary of all API Endpoints.  Each Intrinio API Endpoint contains additional parameters and flexibility, so please review each section to learn how to customize your request to receive the data exactly how you wish.

Method Endpoint Usage
GET /companies Get a list of all companies
GET /companies?ticker={symbol} Get info for a company
GET /companies?query={query-string} Get a list of companies matching legal name
GET /securities Get a list of all securities
GET /securities?ticker={symbol} Get info for a security
GET /securities?query={query-string} Get a list of securities matching security name
GET /securities/search?conditions={conditions} Get a list of securities matching the conditions (screener)
GET /banks Get a list of all banks in the United States
GET /banks?identifier={ticker|rssd_id} Get info for a bank
GET /banks?query={query-string} Get a list of banks matching bank name
GET /banks/holding_companies Get a list of bank holding companies in the US
GET /banks/holding_companies?identifier={ticker|rssd_id} Get info for a bank holding company
GET /banks/holding_companies?query={query-string} Get a list of bank holding companies matching bank name
GET /banks/branches?identifier={ticker|rssd_id} Get a list of bank branches for a bank
GET /banks/branches?uninumber={branch-uninumber} Get info for a specific bank branch office
GET /banks/failed Get a list of all failed banks in the US
GET /indices Get a list of all indices
GET /indices?ticker={symbol} Get info for an index
GET /data_point?ticker={symbol}&item={tag} Get the latest data point for a ticker and a data point tag
GET /data_point?ticker={symbol1,symbol2}&item={tag1,tag2} Get the latest data points for two tickers and two data point tags
GET /historical_data?ticker={symbol}&item={tag} Get time series data for a ticker and historical data tag
GET /prices?ticker={symbol} Get stock price data for a ticker
GET /news?ticker={symbol} Get the latest news for a ticker
GET /fundamentals/standardized?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement} Get a list of fundamentals for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /tags/standardized?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement} Get a list of standardized tags for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /financials/standardized?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement}&fiscal_year={fiscal_year}&fiscal_period={fiscal_period} Get a list of all historical financial data for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /fundamentals/reported?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement} Get a list of reported fundamentals for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /tags/reported?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement} Get a list of reported XBRL tags for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /financials/reported?ticker={symbol}&statement={statement}&fiscal_year={fiscal_year}&fiscal_period={fiscal_period} Get a list of all reported historical financial data for a ticker and a financial statement
GET /fundamentals/banks?identifier={symbol/rssd_id} Get a list of bank call report/UBPR report fundamentals for a ticker or RSSD ID
GET /tags/bank?identifier={symbol/rssd_id}&statement={statement} Get a list of bank XBRL tags for a ticker/rssd_id and a financial statement from the call report or UBPR report
GET /financials/banks?identifier={symbol/rssd_id}&statement={statement}&fiscal_year={fiscal_year}&fiscal_period={fiscal_period} Get a list of all bank historical financial data for a ticker and a financial statement from the call report/UBPR report filings

Here is an example API call:

https://api.intrinio.com/financials/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY

This call has a response of the complete standardized income statement for Apple (AAPL) for the 2014 fiscal year.

The (abbreviated) JSON response would look like this:

Authentication

The Intrinio API uses Basic Authentication over HTTPS.  There are two ways to authenticate:

  1. Create an App (or select the Excel or Google Sheets Apps) in the Data Feed Portal and use the API Username as the username and the API Password as the password, both of which are issued with the App on the Credentials tab.
  2. If you received access as a "Collaborator Only" associated with another User's App, in the Data Feed Portal use the API Username as the username and the API Password as the password, both of which can be found on the Credentials tab of the App.

Authentication in the above API Call example would look as such in a cURL call:

$ curl "https://api.intrinio.com/financials/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY" -u "<API_USERNAME>:<API_PASSWORD>"

As a reminder, if you are using the API directly, the HTTP Basic Authentication must be added to the headers of the request, and encoded using Base64. If you are using a Rest Client, this most likely will be done for by simply adding the username and password to the headers. This is a common error for new users of APIs. If you are using the Excel Add-in or Google Sheets Add-on, this is done for you automatically.

The purpose of this architecture is to enable an administrator to use one subscription and payment method, who can then share access with additional users with all usage attributed to the administrative user.

For example, a Managing Director signed up for a subscription using his or her account to manage the subscription and faciliate payment.  The Managing Director may Create an App to share access with analysts working for the Managing Director.  On the App's page, enter the Analyst's email address to grant Collaborator Access.  After granted access, the Analyst will see their Collaborator Only App, which will contain the API Username and API Password that will grant the Analyst access to the subscription of the Managing Director.  Specifically, this is designed for individuals using the Excel Add-in.

Response Formats

All Intrinio API responses are in JSON format.  The HTTP Response Status Code of 200 indicates that a request is well formed and valid. A Status Code of 401 indicates that API Authorization is not authenticated, due to being invalid.  The Response Status Code of 403 indicates that you have reached a usage limit, such as your subscription's 10 minute call limit or daily call limit.  The Response message will give further indication to the reason for the error.

SDKs

Intrinio currently supports two officially released SDKs, a Microsoft Excel Add-in and a Google Sheets add-on:

Intrinio Microsoft Excel add-in

intrinio-excel-addin (Windows/Mac/GitHub)

Intrinio Google Sheets add-on

intrinio-google-sheets (Chrome Store/GitHub)

In the future, we plan on supporting Ruby, Java, Node.js, Python, PHP, .Net, and Javascript.  We are open to working with developers in the open source community to build and maintain unofficial SDKs that simplify the usage of the Intrinio API in various programming languages.

Node.js

intrinio-client (GitHub/npm)

Operation Summary

Here are the available REST API operations:

Companies

/companies
Returns company list and information for all companies covered by Intrinio.

Parameters

  • ticker (optional, returns full list of companies with compacted response values, if no identifier specified) – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • cik (optional, returns full list of companies with compacted response values, if no identifier specified) – the Central Index Key issued by the SEC, which is the unique identifier all company filings are issued under:
    CENTRAL INDEX KEY
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single company in the list of all companies
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities
  • cik – the Central Index Key issued by the SEC, which is the unique identifier all company filings are issued under
  • name – the company name in shorter form
  • legal_name – the company's official legal name
  • state – the state (US & Canada Only) where the company headquarters is located
  • country – the country where the company headquarters is located
  • inc_state – the state (US & Canada Only) where the company is incorporated
  • inc_country – the country where the company is incorporated
  • sic – the Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) determined by the company filed with the SEC
  • stock_exchange – the Stock Exchange where the company's common stock is primarily traded
  • template – the financial statement template used by Intrinio to standardize the as reported data
  • short_description – a one or two sentance description of the company's operations
  • long_description – a one paragraph description of the company's operations and other corporate actions
  • ceo – the Chief Executive Officer of the company
  • company_url – the url to the company's primary corporate website or primary internet property
  • business_address – the company's headquarters address
  • mailing_address – the mailing address reported by the company
  • business_phone_no – the phone number reported by the company
  • employees – the number of employees working for the company
  • sector – the company's operating sector (All Sectors)
  • industry_category – the company's operating industry category (All Industry Categories)
  • industry_group – the company's operating industry group (All Industry Groups)
  • standardized_active – if true, the company has standardized and as reported fundamental data via the Intrinio API; if false, the company has as reported data only.
  • valuation_active – if true, the company is currently available on the intrinio valuation webapp, otherwise it is not available.

Securities

/securities
Returns security list and information for all securities covered by Intrinio.

Parameters

  • ticker (optional, returns full list of companies with compacted response values, if no identifier specified) – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities
  • security_name – the security description as provided by the exchange
  • security_type – the type of security, such as Common Stock, Preferred Stock, Warrants, Limited Partnership Interests, etc.
  • security_class – if a company has multiple securities, the security class is a single letter description of the class of a certain type of security.
  • stock_exchange – the Stock Exchange (and market category) where the company's common stock is primarily traded
  • listing_exchange – the Stock Exchange where the company's common stock is primarily traded
  • market_category – the Nasdaq market category for a Nasdaq listed company.
  • etf – true or false, depending on whether the security is an ETF or not.
  • round_lot_size – the round lot size for the security.
  • financial_status – indicates when an issuer has failed to submit its regulatory filings on a timely basis, has failed to meet NASDAQ's continuing listing standards, and/or has filed for bankruptcy. Values include: D = Deficient: Issuer Failed to Meet NASDAQ Continued Listing Requirements, E = Delinquent: Issuer Missed Regulatory Filing Deadline, Q = Bankrupt: Issuer Has Filed for Bankruptcy, N = Normal (Default): Issuer Is NOT Deficient, Delinquent, or Bankrupt., G = Deficient and Bankrupt, H = Deficient and Delinquent, J = Delinquent and Bankrupt, K = Deficient, Delinquent, and Bankrupt
  • primary_security – true if the subject security is the primary security for the company. If a security is the default, the ticker symbol for the security is the same as the ticker for the company (see /Companies endpoint).
  • delisted_security – if the security is no longer traded on public exchanges, the security will be considered delisted and the security no longer will report pricing data.
  • last_crsp_adj_date – the last recorded date ("YYYY-MM-DD") of an CRSP adjustment made to prior prices due to a stock split or dividend event.

Securities Search/Screener

/securities/search
Returns security list and information all securities that match the given conditions. The API call credits required for each call is equal to the number of conditions specified.

Parameters

  • conditions – A comma-separated list of conditions. Each condition consists three elements separated by tildes (~):
    • A data tag INTRINIO TAGS
    • An operator
      • Equal to: "eq"
      • Greater than: "gt"
      • Greater than or equal to: "gte"
      • Less than: "lt"
      • Less than or equal to: "lte"
      • Contains text: "contains"
    • A value
  • order_column – A data tag by which to order the results INTRINIO TAGS
  • order_direction – The direction in which to order the results ("asc" for Ascending or "desc" for descending)
  • page_size – (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page (up to 100)
  • page_number – (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values

Return Values

The return values will correspond to the data tags in the conditions. Ticker will always be included.

Example Requests

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /securities/search
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/securities/search?conditions=open_price~gt~10.50,pricetoearnings~gt~10

Indices

/indices
Returns indices list and information for all indices covered by Intrinio.

Parameters

  • ticker (optional, returns full list of indices with compacted response values if no ticker or identifier specified) – the Intrinio symbol associated with the index: INDEX SYMBOL
  • identifier (optional, returns full list of indices with compacted response values if no ticker or identifier specified) – the Intrinio identifier associated with the index: INDEX SYMBOL
  • type (optional, returns full list of indices otherwise) – the type of indices specificed: stock_market | economic
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • symbol – the Intrinio symbol associated with the index
  • index_name – the index name
  • country – the country of focus for the index

Data Point

/data_point
Returns that most recent data point for a selected identifier (ticker symbol, index symbol, CIK ID, Federal Reserve Economic Data Series ID, etc.) for a selected tag.  The complete list of tags available through this function are available here.  Income statement, cash flow statement, and ratios are returned as trailing twelve months values.  All other data points are returned as their most recent value, either as of the last release financial statement or the most recent reported value.

Parameters

  • ticker – (optional, must enter an identifier otherwise) the stock market ticker symbol associated with the company's common stock or index.  If the company is foreign, use the stock exchange code, followed by a colon, then the ticker.  You may request up to 150 tickers at once by separating them by a coma (each ticker and item combination requested will count as 1 query of the API): TICKER SYMBOL | INDEX SYMBOL | EXCHANGE:TICKER
  • identifier – (optional, must enter a ticker otherwise) an identifier for the company or data point, including the SEC CIK ID, FRED Series ID, or Damodaran ERP. You may request up to 150 companies at once by separating them by a coma (each ticker and item combination requested will count as 1 query of the API): CENTRAL INDEX KEY | FRED.GDP | DMD.ERP | TICKER SYMBOL | INDEX SYMBOL | EXCHANGE:TICKER
  • item – the specified standardized tag or series ID requested.  You may request up to 150 tags at once by separating them by a coma (each ticker and item combination requested will count as 1 query of the API):  INTRINIO TAGS | FRED SERIES IDs | DAMODARAN ERP

Return Values

  • identifier – the ticker or identifier for the data point
  • item – the requested standardized tag or series ID
  • value – the value of the Intrinio tag of the financial data point

Historical Data

/historical_data
Returns that historical data for for a selected identifier (ticker symbol or index symbol) for a selected tag.  The complete list of tags available through this function are available here.  Income statement, cash flow statement, and ratios are returned as trailing twelve months values by default, but can be changed with the type parametrer.  All other historical data points are returned as their value on a certain day based on filings reported as of that date.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the company's common stock or index.  If the company is foreign, use the stock exchange code, followed by a colon, then the ticker.  You may request up to 150 tickers at once by separating them by a coma (each ticker and item combination requested will count as 1 query of the API): TICKER SYMBOL | INDEX SYMBOL | FRED SYMBOL | SIC SYMBOL
  • item – the specified standardized tag requested.  INTRINIO TAGS | ECONOMIC TAGS
  • sort_order – (optional, default=desc) – the order of the historical stock price dates: asc | desc
  • start_date (optional) – the first date in which historical stock prices are delivered – historical daily prices go back to 1996 for most companies, but some go back further to the 1970s or to the date of the IPO: YYYY-MM-DD
  • end_date (optional, default=today) – the last date in which historical stock prices are delivered – end of day prices are available around 5 p.m. EST and 15 minute delayed prices are updated every minute throughout the trading day: YYYY-MM-DD
  • type (optional, returns trailing twelve months (TTM) for the income statement, cash flow statement and calculations, and quarterly (QTR) for balance sheet) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data and trailing twelve months for annual data on a quarterly basis: FY | QTR | TTM | YTD
  • stat (optional, must enter for any query of the SIC Indices to indicate the response type) – the type of statistic requested when querying using the SIC Indices: count | sum | max | 75thpctl | mean | median | 25thpctl | min
  • frequency (optional, returns daily historical price data otherwise) – the frequency of the historical prices & valuation data: daily | weekly | monthly | quarterly | yearly
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • identifier – the ticker or identifier for the data point
  • item – the requested standardized tag or series ID
  • date – the date associated with the value of the data tag
  • value – the value of the Intrinio tag of the financial data point

Prices

/prices
Returns professional-grade historical stock prices for a security or stock market index.  New EOD prices are available at 5p.m. EST and 15 minute delayed prices are updated every minute during the trading day.  Historical prices are available back to 1996 or the IPO data in most cases, with some companies with data back to the 1970s.  Stock market index historical price data is available back to the 1950s at the earliest. Data from Quandl, QuoteMedia and the Federal Reserve Economic Data.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities or the stock market index: TICKER SYMBOL | INDEX SYMBOL
  • sort_order – (optional, default=desc) – the order of the historical stock price dates: asc | desc
  • start_date (optional) – the first date in which historical stock prices are delivered – historical daily prices go back to 1996 for most companies, but some go back further to the 1970s or to the date of the IPO: YYYY-MM-DD
  • end_date (optional, default=today) – the last date in which historical stock prices are delivered – end of day prices are available around 5 p.m. EST and 15 minute delayed prices are updated every minute throughout the trading day: YYYY-MM-DD
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single stock historical stock price data point from the first entry, based on sort order
  • frequency (optional, returns daily historical price data otherwise) – the frequency of the historical prices: daily | weekly | monthly | quarterly | yearly
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • date – the date of the stock price historical data
  • open – the actual observed first traded stock price of the trading date
  • high – the actual observed highest traded stock price on the trading date
  • low – the actual observed lowest traded stock price on the trading date
  • close – the actual observed last trade stock price on the trading date
  • volume – the actual observed number of shares of stock traded between market participants of the trading date
  • ex_dividend – the non-split adjusted dividend per share on the ex-dividend date – not available on index historical prices
  • split_ratio – the split factor on the split date – not available on index historical prices
  • adj_open – the dividend and split adjusted open price – not available on index historical prices
  • adj_high – the dividend and split adjusted high price – not available on index historical prices
  • adj_low – the dividend and split adjusted low price – not available on index historical prices
  • adj_close – the dividend and split adjusted close price – not available on index historical prices
  • adj_volume – the dividend and split adjusted volume – not available on index historical prices

Company News

/news
Returns the most recent news stories for a company.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the company's common stock.  If the company is foreign, use the stock exchange code, followed by a colon, then the ticker.  You may request up to 10 tickers at once by separating them with a coma: TICKER SYMBOL | EXCHANGE:TICKER

Return Values

  • title – the title of the article
  • publication_date – the date the article was published
  • url – the hyperlink to the article
  • summary – a brief summary of the article

Standardized Fundamentals

/fundamentals/standardized
Returns a list of available standardized fundamentals (fiscal year and fiscal period) for a given ticker and statement.  Also, you may add a date and type parameter to specify the fundamentals you wish to be returned in the response.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • statement – the financial statement requested, options include the income statement, balance sheet, statement of cash flows and calculated metrics and ratios : income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement | calculations
  • type (optional, returns all available fundamentals) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data and trailing twelve months for annual data on a quarterly basis: FY | QTR | TTM | YTD
  • date (optional, default=today) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single fundamental from the first entry
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • fiscal_year – the fiscal year of the fundamental
  • fiscal_period – the fiscal period of the fundamental
  • end_date – the last date of the fundamental
  • start_date – (not available on the balance sheet) the first date of the fundamental

Example Requests

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /fundamentals/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&type=FY
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/fundamentals/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&type=FY

Standardized Tags and Labels

/tags/standardized
Returns the As Reported XBRL tags and labels for a given ticker, statement, and date or fiscal year/fiscal quarter.

A basic list of all industrial standardized tags can be found here.
A basic list of all financial standardized tags can be found here.

Parameters

  • statement – the financial statement requested, options include the income statement, balance sheet, statement of cash flows, calculated metrics and ratios, and current data points : income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement | calculations | current
  • template (optional, must include a ticker if not specified) – the financial statement tag template: industrial | financial
  • ticker (optional, must include a template if not specified) – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single tag from the first entry, based on order
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • name – the readable name of the tag
  • tag – the Intrinio standardized tag
  • parent – the parent Intrinio standardized tag forming the statement relationship with the factor.
  • factor – the operator forming the statement relationship between the child tag (or tags) and the parent.
  • balance – the accounting balance (debit or credit) of the tag
  • type – the nature of the tag, operating or nonoperating
  • units – the unit of the tag

Standardized Financials

/financials/standardized
Returns professional-grade historical financial data.  This data is standardized, cleansed and verified to ensure the highest quality data sourced directly from the XBRL financial statements.  The primary purpose of standardized financials are to facilitate comparability across a single company's fundamentals and across all companies fundamentals.

For example, it is possible to compare total revenues between two companies as of a certain point in time, or within a single company across multiple time periods.  This is not possible using the as reported financial statements because of the inherent complexity of reporting standards.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • statement – the financial statement requested, options include the income statement, balance sheet, statement of cash flows and calculated metrics and ratios: income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement | calculations
  • tag (optional, default is all tags) – the specified standardized tag: STANDARDIZED INDUSTRIAL TAGS | STANDARDIZED FINANCIAL TAGS
  • fiscal_year (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal year associated with the fundamental: YYYY
  • fiscal_period (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal period associated with the fundamental: FY | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1TTM | Q2TTM | Q3TTM | Q2YTD | Q3YTD
  • type (optional,  must specify a date or must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data and trailing twelve months for annual data on a quarterly basis: FY | QTR | TTM | YTD
  • date (optional,  otherwise, must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • tag – the Intrinio standardized tag of the financial data point
  • value – the value of the Intrinio tag of the financial data point

Example Request

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /financials/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/financials/standardized?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY

As Reported Fundamentals

/fundamentals/reported
Returns a list of available as reported fundamentals (fiscal year, fiscal period, start date, and end date) for a given ticker and statement.  Also, you may add a date and type parameter to specify the fundamentals you wish to be returned in the response.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • statement – the financial statement requested, options include the income statement, balance sheet and statement of cash flows: income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement
  • type (optional, returns all available fundamentals) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data: FY | QTR
  • date (optional, default=today) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single fundamental from the first entry
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • fiscal_year – the fiscal year of the fundamental
  • fiscal_period – the fiscal period of the fundamental
  • end_date – the last date of the fundamental
  • start_date – (not available on the balance sheet) the first date of the fundamental

As Reported XBRL Tags and Labels

/tags/reported
Returns the As Reported XBRL tags and labels for a given ticker, statement, and date or fiscal year/fiscal quarter.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • statement – the financial statement requested: income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement
  • fiscal_year (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal year associated with the fundamental: YYYY
  • fiscal_period (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal period associated with the fundamental: FY | Q1 | Q2 | Q3
  • type (optional,  must specify a date or must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data and trailing twelve months for annual data on a quarterly basis: FY | QTR
  • date (optional,  otherwise, must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • name – the label of the XBRL tag as reported of the financial statement
  • tag – the XBRL tag of the associated financial data point
  • balance – the accounting balance (debit or credit) of the tag
  • unit – the unit type of the XBRL tag
  • domain_tag – the specified domain XBRL tag, associated with certain data points on the financial statements that have a dimension associated with the data point
  • abstract – the type of value – true indicates that the value is a header label and has no associated data value, whereas false indicates that the XBRL tag has an associated value.
  • sequence – an integer 0 or greater indicating the presentation order of the XBRL tag and label in the financial statement
  • depth – an integer 0 or greater indicating the presentation indentation depth of the XBRL tag and label in the financial statement

As Reported Financials

/financials/reported
Returns the As Reported Financials directly from the financial statements of the XBRL filings from the company.

Parameters

  • ticker – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities: TICKER SYMBOL
  • statement – the financial statement requested, options include the income statement, balance sheet, statement of cash flows and calculated metrics and ratios : income_statement | balance_sheet | cash_flow_statement
  • xbrl_tag (optional, default is all tags) – the specified XBRL tag
  • domain_tag (optional) – the specified domain XBRL tag, associated with certain data points on the financial statements that have a dimension associated with the data point
  • fiscal_year (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal year associated with the fundamental: YYYY
  • fiscal_period (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal period associated with the fundamental: FY | Q1 | Q2 | Q3
  • type (optional,  must specify a date or must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data and trailing twelve months for annual data on a quarterly basis: FY | QTR
  • date (optional,  otherwise, must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • xbrl_tag – the reported XBRL tag of the financial data point
  • value – the value of the XBRL tag of the financial data point

Example Request

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /financials/reported?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/financials/reported?ticker=AAPL&statement=income_statement&fiscal_year=2014&fiscal_period=FY

Bank Fundamentals

/fundamentals/banks
Returns a list of available bank fundamentals (fiscal year, fiscal period, start date, and end date) for a given ticker/rssd_id and statement.  Statements are from the bank call report and UBPR reports filed with the FDIC & Federal Reserve.  Also, you may add a date and type parameter to specify the fundamentals you wish to be returned in the response.

Parameters

  • ticker/rssd_id/identifier – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities, or the bank/bank holding company RSSD ID issued by the Federal Reserve: TICKER SYMBOL | RSSD ID LOOKUP
  • statement – (optional, returns all available statements) – the call report/UBPR financial statement requested
  • report – (optional, returns both call report and UBPR reports) – select report for all fundamentas:  call_report | ubpr
  • type (optional, returns all available fundamentals) – the type of periods requested – includes fiscal years for annual data, quarters for quarterly data: FY | QTR | YTD
  • date (optional, default=today) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • sequence (optional, returns full list without a sequence number) – an integer 0 or greater for calling a single fundamental from the first entry
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • statement_code – the statement code for the financial statement from the report
  • fiscal_year – the fiscal year of the fundamental
  • fiscal_period – the fiscal period of the fundamental
  • end_date – the last date of the fundamental
  • start_date – (not available on the balance sheet) the first date of the fundamental
  • report – the report the financial statement is sourced from, cooresponding with the statement_code

Example Requests

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /fundamentals/banks?ticker=STT&type=FY
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/fundamentals/banks?ticker=STT&type=FY

Bank XBRL Tags and Labels

/tags/banks
Returns the Bank XBRL tags and labels for a given ticker/RSSD ID, statement, and date or fiscal year/fiscal quarter.

Parameters

  • ticker/rssd_id/identifier – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities, or the bank/bank holding company RSSD ID issued by the Federal Reserve: TICKER SYMBOL | RSSD ID LOOKUP
  • statement – the financial statement requested from the call report or the UBPR report, which can be found from the bank fundamentals end point.
  • fiscal_year (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal year associated with the fundamental: YYYY
  • fiscal_period (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal period associated with the fundamental: FY | Q1 | Q2YTD | Q3YTD
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • name – the label of the XBRL tag as reported of the financial statement
  • tag – the XBRL tag of the associated financial data point
  • unit – the unit type of the XBRL tag
  • abstract – the type of value – true indicates that the value is a header label and has no associated data value, whereas false indicates that the XBRL tag has an associated value.
  • sequence – an integer 0 or greater indicating the presentation order of the XBRL tag and label in the financial statement
  • depth – an integer 0 or greater indicating the presentation indentation depth of the XBRL tag and label in the financial statement

Example Request

API URI: https://api.intrinio.com
GET: /tags/reported?banks=STT&statement=ri&fiscal_year=2015&fiscal_period=FY
FULL URL: https://api.intrinio.com/tags/banks?ticker=STT&statement=ri&fiscal_year=2015&fiscal_period=FY

Bank Financials

/financials/banks
Returns the Bank Financials directly from the financial statements of the call report and UBPR report XBRL filings from the bank issued with the FDIC.

Parameters

  • ticker/rssd_id/identifier – the stock market ticker symbol associated with the companies common stock securities, or the bank/bank holding company RSSD ID issued by the Federal Reserve: TICKER SYMBOL | RSSD ID LOOKUP
  • statement – the financial statement requested from the call report or the UBPR report, which can be found from the bank fundamentals end point.
  • fiscal_year (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal year associated with the fundamental: YYYY
  • fiscal_period (optional,  otherwise, must specify a date) – the fiscal period associated with the fundamental: FY | Q1 | Q2YTD | Q3YTD
  • tag (optional, default is all tags) – the specified bank call report or UBPR report XBRL tag
  • date (optional,  otherwise, must specify a fiscal year and fiscal period) – the first fundamental will be the latest as of this specified date: YYYY-MM-DD
  • page_size (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the number of results on each page.
  • page_number (optional, returns full list without a page size & number) – an integer greater than 1 for specifying the page number for the return values.

Return Values

  • tag – the bank call report or UBPR report XBRL tag of the financial data point
  • value – the value of the XBRL tag of the financial data point
